title: Webb schedules presser to discuss campaign
text:
Webb schedules presser to discuss campaign Former senator to announce he is considering running for president as an independent UPDATED 8:01 PM CDT Oct 19, 2015 Photos Scott Olson Getty Images 
Jim Webb is holding a news conference Tuesday to announce he is considering running for president as an independent -- rather than a Democrat. Videos Clinton sent GOP 2016ers copies of... 
The former Virginia senator complained repeatedly during last week's first Democratic presidential debate that he wasn't being given enough time to speak. Former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton and Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders -- the two contenders dominating in the polls -- were the focus of attention, he contended. 
Webb is holding his news conference at 1 p.m. ET at the National Press Club. 
His campaign is billing it as a discussion of "his candidacy, the campaign and his views of the political parties in the current election cycle."
